New York Investors May Buy Pittsburgh U.S. Steel Tower, WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-02-16T04:46:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/new-york-investors-may-buy-pittsburgh-u-s-steel-tower-wsj-says.html
A group of New York investors led by
Mark Karasick reached a tentative agreement to buy the U.S.
Steel Tower in Pittsburgh in a deal worth $250 million, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter.  The building is being sold by a group including AREA
Property Partners and Winthrop Realty Partners; the deal is
conditional on the buyers lining up finance and may yet
collapse, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  